: "text", "text": ": see the next paragraph, in three places."}], "source_refs": []}, {"entry_id": "n13400", "headword_ar": "دُوَارٌ", "root": "dwr", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A vertigo,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "giddiness in the head;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, * A, * K;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dawaArN", "text_ar": "دَوَارٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (M, K.)       -A2-  Also, and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dawaArN", "text_ar": "دَوَارٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ald~uwaAru", "text_ar": "الدُّوَارُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ald~awaAru", "text_ar": "الدَّوَارُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (T, M, K,) and (but less commonly, TA) ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ald~uw~aAru", "text_ar": "الدُّوَّارُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ald~aw~aAru", "text_ar": "الدَّوَّارُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain idol,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S, M, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which the Arabs set up, and around it they made a space,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "round which they turned, or circled:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, M:) and the same name they applied to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the space above mentioned:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, M:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it is said that they thus compassed it certain weeks, like as people compass the Kaabeh:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(MF:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "certain stones around which they circled, in imitation of people compassing the Kaabeh."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAmb.) Imra-el- Keys says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "Ea*aAraY duwaArK fiY mulaA='K mu*ay~ali"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Virgins"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "making the circuit"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of Duwár, in"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 932}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "long-skirted garments of the kind called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mulaA='", "text_ar": "مُلَا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S:) likening a herd of [wild] cows to damsels thus occupied and attired, alluding to the length of their tails. (TA.) ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ald~uw~aAru", "text_ar": "الدُّوَّارُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ald~aw~aAru", "text_ar": "الدَّوَّارُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signify"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The Kaabeh."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Kr, M, K.) And ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "duw~aArN", "text_ar": "دُوَّارٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Th, M, [not"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "duw~aArapN", "text_ar": "دُوَّارَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as is implied in the K,])"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A circling tract"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "musotadaAr", "text_ar": "مُسْتَدَار", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of sand, around which go the wild animals:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Th, M, K:) a poet says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "bid~uwaAri nihoY *iY EaraArK waHul~abi"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "In the sandy tract around a pool of water left by a torrent, containing plants of the kinds called 'arár and hullab"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Th, M.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "T", "M", "K", "MF", "Th"]}, {"entry_id": "n13404", "headword_ar": "دَوَّارٌ", "root": "dwr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Turning round, circling,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "revolving,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] applied to the firmament, or celestial orb. (A.) ―         -b2-  Applied likewise to time, or fortune; (M, K;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daw~aAriY~N", "text_ar": "دَوَّارِىٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, M, A, K,) which is said to be a rel. n., but is not so accord. to AAF, though having the form thereof, like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kurosiY~N", "text_ar": "كُرْسِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M,) the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Y", "text_ar": "ى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being a corroborative: (Msb voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waHo$iY~N", "text_ar": "وَحْشِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) thus in the saying,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "↓ \n      waAld~ahoru biA@loA_inosaAni daw~aAriY~u"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, * A, * K, *) occurring in a poem of El-'Ajjáj, (S,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daw~aArN", "text_ar": "دَوَّارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, K,) i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And time,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fortune, turns man about from one state,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "condition, to another:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, * A, K: *) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "turns him about much."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wH$", "text_ar": "وحش"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".)       -A2-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "duwaArN", "text_ar": "دُوَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in two places."}], "source_refs": ["S", "M", "A", "K"]}, {"entry_id": "n13405", "headword_ar": "دُوَّارٌ", "root": "dwr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "duwaArN", "text_ar": "دُوَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in three places."}], "source_refs": []}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_a